Exercises.ExerciseDescription: Hold a dumbbell in each hand. Alternating arms, slowly raise the dumbbell to your chest, making sure to keep your elbows at your side.

ExerciseVideoLink.ExerciseDescription: Hold a dumbbell in each hand. Take a large step forward with one foot, keeping your other foot planted. Lower yourself until your rear knee nearly touches the ground. Repeat with your other leg.
Sit on the exercise machine, such that your calves are resting on the leg rest. Bend your knees, pressing the leg rest downward until your legs create a 90 degree angle.

Hold a dumbbell in each hand. Lay on your back atop an excercise bench with your arms out to your side; your arms should be slightly bent. Without bending your elbows, raise the dumbells directly above you.
Hold a dumbbell in each hand, with an overhand grip. Keeping your arms straight, alternate raising each dumbbell up to shoulder level in front of you.
Lay on the exercise bench with the bar directly above your head. Slowly lower the barbell, letting it breifly touch your chest before raising it back up.
Gripping the dip bars lift your feet off the ground. Lower your body as far as possible without letting your feet touch the ground. Raise yourself back up and repeat.
rip the pull-up bar with an underhand grip. Lifting your feet off the ground, pull yourself up until your chin is level with the bar.
